A vintage-style illustration of a sleek silver solid-state drive sitting on a wooden desk, with a large brass padlock clamped around it. The padlock is rusted and jammed, with a broken key stuck in the keyhole. Behind the drive, an old-fashioned rotary telephone sits off the hook, its coiled cord dangling uselessly. The scene is lit by warm amber light from a green banker's lamp, casting long shadows. The color palette features muted browns, aged creams, and tarnished metallics, evoking 1940s office equipment catalogs. Small dust particles float in the light beam, and the desk surface shows wear marks and coffee ring stains, suggesting prolonged frustration and waiting.
